  "notes": "Apulian (Pugliese). Southern Italo-Romance of Puglia. N. Puglia patterns with the Neapolitan continuum, S. Puglia (Salento) has stronger Greek substrate. Key features: (1) Vowel reduction to [ə]. (2) Metaphony. (3) Centralised [ɐ] in unstressed position (Barese). (4) Griko still spoken in Grecìa Salentina (Fanciullo 2015, Ledgeway 2009).",
